column5: Hey guys.... what's the weather like in your area??  here, up in the Outaouais, been raining all day and now @8:55pm the rain just subsided and looks like it's clearing up  Leechman

Rain has stopped here as well for now.  But it's supposed to start again for the next couple of days.  Makes painting inside the house not feel as bad.  If we get a break from the rain tomorrow I have to winterize the pop-up trailer and maybe go fetch the snowmobile and make sure she's all ready to go.  Cheers  Craig
Next to nothing to speak of all day in London.  Had expected rain all day but it just never happened.  Bright and sunny in the morning and then gloomy the next minute.

Thanks for reporting guys.  Was suppose to change the oil in the snow blower today, finish the work in the back yard and planting the garlic but the rain    just poured down and instead gotten into preparing meals for my vacation next week, deer hunting.  Got spaghetti sauce, lasagna and sheppard pie done.  Leaving Oct 31st and coming back Nov 10th.  Good luck to all of the hunters on this board and tight lines to the fishermen  Leechman

crappy enough right now, that as of about 12:30 when I got in from work..we cancelled the fishin trip we where go go out on in my boat this morning.  Windy as crap...storm clouds rolling in as I type  ..suppost to be strong SW winds..just enough to kick up Erie enough that it will dirty up the  lower river for a couple days
Right now it's 37.9*F with a pea soup fog, s'posed to go up to 73*F with bright sunshine and winds out of the NW @5-10 mph.  I'll be tilling up a landscaped area in the front yard today.
nooo i want the rain for today, i just went out and bought a nice big rain suit
southern ontario . major wind advisory. a good day to work on baits. waves 3-5ft.
Yikessss 3-5ft waves     wise decision to stay off the water...... Here right now it's sunny, temp @5*C with 4 Km/h winds from the east.  Definitely will be working outside today.  Leechman

at the moment its rain and wind...wind due to get upto 35kms today...so much for my fishing plans...lol...i might brave it though.    LIVE WEATHER SHOT FROM MY COMPUTER DESK WINDOW...GREY, WET AND WINDY...WOW...JUST LIKE ENGLAND AGAIN!!!!....LOL
WOW bet you can't resist with a view like this    Very nice Wish I was closer to the water right now
its a constant struggle Leechman...lol.....the water....it speaks to me.......calls me.
Well then..... what your waiting for.... go get'em
ok....i'll just get outta my PJs and head down...see what if anything i can catch in an hour...will do a mini report in 60minutes time....lol.
Winter arrived yesterday Currently it is -10C with 30KM winds and -17C windchill. On a positive note I may be ice fishing by next weekend!!!
OMG     Already!!  Just a little nippy up there Drifter What is the species you target when ice fishing??
Lakers, Pike, Walleye, Whitefish and Ling. But I'm mainly a Laker guy.
Cool.... thanks for the info      If you're able to go ice fishing next weekend, tight lines and good luck  I'll be watching for the first hard water report

i'll be watching for a hard water report too....your a lucky man Drifter...wow..icefishing in October...how  excellent...i love fishing for lakers too....whitefish being my second favourite target species.

The weather here is dull raining heard thunder recently. I am glad I got a burst of energy yesterday after doing the weekly Saturday morning work and then home chores. I went steelhead fishing during the break in the weather for 11 hrs and got skunked. I would have upset if I woke up this morning and it wasn't crappy weather LOL.
Sorry to hear about the skunk Canuck     11hrs is a lot of time spent without a bite but at least you got out  Thanks for info

I for 1,am getting tired of the forcasts that DO NOT come true. Yesturday they called for showers later in the day,so I get up,head for a deer hunt and it starts pouring . Today they call for rain all morning so I sleep in,make plans for the gym,wake up and skies are clear. How much do these guys get paid to screw with us.LOL
Yeah I hear ya...... kind of wonder some times but dunno Did you see anything while out for deer? Is it bow or riffle? Leechman
